WorldStage Newsonlineâ€“ DEAP Capital Management & Trust Plc, a Nigeria-based fund management company which operates in the capital market, mortgage banking, and oil and gas sectors has blamed a pending controversy instigated by certain shareholders of the company represented by a law firm, Ascendo Law for the cancellation of its re-scheduled 11th Annual General Meeting (AGM) earlier scheduled for 31st December 2020. In a notification at the Nigerian Stock Exchange dated February 19th, 2021 signed by Fetunde Fashesin, Company Secretary said the board of the directors decided not to represent the company in general meetings and duly deferred to the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) for further action. WorldStage reported on February 22, 2021 that SEC appointed an Interim Management Team (IMT) to oversee the affairs of the company following the resignation of the board of directors.